      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LENNY'S HONEY (1) goes very well at the course and distance with two wins and a placing from four starts. Scored by 0.8 lengths last time (19.50) in a OPEN over 342m at Angle Park. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. PAW MANTRA (2) showed strong early pace from the wide draw and stuck on well despite missing the frame, finishing fifth over 400m this track in 23.19. Has ability and can measure up. TERRIFIC BAZ (4) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fourth (23.19) last time in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning four races. A big run wouldn't surprise. CHICKEN KNIGHT (5) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
